row.Content_Text: I would not rely on this kit since it did not work for me and worsened my skin. You should look into Peter Thomas Roth's Laser-Free Resurfacer for any uneven skintones (ance, acne marks, as well as wrinkles). Additionally make sure you're exfoliating you skin 1-3 times a week and moisturizing you skin. People think that you should not moisturize with acne but your sebaceous glands will compensate from the lack of moisture and you'll end up with more acne AND oilier skin. This kit is great for someone who has no skin problems, for instance a 10-year-old, but for us girls with acne we need products that work. Using a deep-cleaning gel or milk cleanser will be enough if you're using a Clarisonic (these are great with acne because you aren't actually cleansing you skin using your fingers or a washcloth). On that note, make sure you are effectively removing your makeup prior to using a Clarisonic and if you use it to remove you makeup, wash your face twice! For acne treatment I would recommend something simple and antibacterial, for instance tea tree oil, especially if you are making any extractions. Basically, make sure you are using the right techniques with your acne-prone skin if you want to improve your complexion because you cannot rely on a kit to change you skin too much. Something that's helped me the most has been taking 2 50MG pills of Spironolactone which was prescribed for me from my dermatologist after months of insane hormonal breakouts. This pill is not intense, like accutane, and isn't an antibiotic like most acne pills. Try some of these and you won't need to rely on a kit and if you use the Clarisonic you skin will be transformed within one year. It's an investment but has transformed so many people's faces, including my own. Best of luck!!
